{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"05fab18a-9c56-4ab7-8cec-efbef84e3fd2","content":"Use `dotnet watch test` with the `--filter` option:\n\n```bash\ndotnet watch test --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~ProcessPayment_NegativeAmount_ThrowsException\"\n```\n\nThis will:\n- **`dotnet watch test`** — re-run tests automatically on file save (hot reload)\n- **`--filter \"FullyQualifiedName~...\"`** — only run tests whose name contains that string\n\nThe `~` operator means \"contains\", so you don't need the full namespace. You can also filter by just the method name:\n\n```bash\ndotnet watch test --filter \"Name=ProcessPayment_NegativeAmount_ThrowsException\"\n```","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"e32818da-7e26-4ab9-8c7a-41d49778eda3","outputTokens":165,"requestId":"67C2:13C959:2C11D1B:30D4D5C:69FD427D"},"id":"8cde6dcc-49a9-41c4-b0cc-23b0882896b7","timestamp":"2026-05-08T01:55:17.951Z","parentId":"aaec08e5-6a43-4d6a-bf04-f0c2216d34e1"}
